---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-second-opinions', text: 'Why Second Opinions Matter', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Plan Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'how-it-works', text: 'How It Works', level: 2 },
  { id: 'when-to-seek', text: 'When to Seek Second Opinions', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Premium Insurance', href: '/best/premium-insurance' },
  { title: 'Cancer Coverage Insurance', href: '/best/cancer-coverage-insurance' },
  { title: 'Network Size Insurance', href: '/best/network-size-insurance' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'secondOpinion', header: 'Second Opinion' },
  { key: 'specialists', header: 'Specialist Access' },
  { key: 'international', header: 'International Experts' },
  { key: 'included', header: 'Included In' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', secondOpinion: 'Yes', specialists: 'Global network', international: 'Yes', included: 'Most plans' },
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', secondOpinion: 'Yes', specialists: 'Wide network', international: 'Yes', included: 'Premium plans' },
  { provider: 'Aetna International', secondOpinion: 'Yes', specialists: 'Strong US', international: 'Yes', included: 'Select plans' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', secondOpinion: 'Limited', specialists: 'Good network', international: 'Limited', included: 'Premium plans' },
  { provider: 'IMG Global', secondOpinion: 'No', specialists: 'Basic', international: 'No', included: 'N/A' },
];

const scenarioColumns = [
  { key: 'scenario', header: 'Scenario' },
  { key: 'value', header: 'Second Opinion Value' },
  { key: 'outcome', header: 'Potential Outcome' },
];

const scenarioRows = [
  { scenario: 'Cancer diagnosis', value: 'Very high', outcome: 'Treatment approach may differ significantly' },
  { scenario: 'Recommended surgery', value: 'High', outcome: 'May find less invasive alternatives' },
  { scenario: 'Chronic condition', value: 'Medium-High', outcome: 'Different management approaches possible' },
  { scenario: 'Rare disease', value: 'Very high', outcome: 'Specialists may have different expertise' },
  { scenario: 'Mental health diagnosis', value: 'Medium', outcome: 'Treatment plans vary by approach' },
  { scenario: 'Routine procedure', value: 'Low', outcome: 'Usually consensus on standard treatments' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="5 Best Expat Insurance Plans with Second Opinion Services (2026)"
  description="Compare 5 international health plans with expert second opinion services. Access world-class specialists for major diagnoses—coverage details compared."
  headline="Best Expat Insurance with Second Opinion Services"
  subheadline="Major diagnoses deserve expert review. Here are the international health plans that include second opinion services from world-class specialists."
  heroImage="/images/answers/best-second-opinion-insurance.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  showHeroCta={false}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Plans"
  ctaButtonHref="/compare/"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Top Picks for Second Opinion Services</h2>
  <p>
    These insurers offer the best second opinion benefits:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🔬</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Second Opinion Services</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Comprehensive second opinion service with access to world-leading specialists included on most plans.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🏥</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Specialist Network</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Strong specialist network for second opinions with good coordination services.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🇺🇸</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best US Specialist Access</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Aetna International</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Access to US medical centers of excellence for second opinions on complex cases.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">💡</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why It Matters</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Peace of Mind</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Studies show 10-30% of diagnoses change after second opinions. Major decisions deserve expert review.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="why-second-opinions">Why Second Opinions Matter</h2>
  <p>
    Second opinions can significantly impact your healthcare:
  </p>

  <h3>Diagnoses Can Change</h3>
  <p>
    Research shows second opinions change outcomes:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>10-30% of diagnoses are modified after second opinion</li>
    <li>Up to 60% of treatment plans change in complex cases</li>
    <li>Cancer diagnoses particularly benefit from review</li>
    <li>Surgical recommendations may have alternatives</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Especially Important Abroad</h3>
  <p>
    Expats face unique challenges:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Local doctors may have different training</li>
    <li>Treatment approaches vary by country</li>
    <li>Language barriers can affect communication</li>
    <li>Access to latest treatments may be limited</li>
    <li>Specialists in rare conditions may not be local</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Major Decisions Deserve Review</h3>
  <p>
    When stakes are high, expert review provides:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Confirmation of diagnosis accuracy</li>
    <li>Alternative treatment options</li>
    <li>Access to specialists in your condition</li>
    <li>Peace of mind for difficult decisions</li>
    <li>Potential cost savings from avoiding unnecessary procedures</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Expert Review"
    description="Compare plans with second opinion services for major diagnoses."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Second Opinion Coverage Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Bupa Global — Best Second Opinion Services</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers the most comprehensive second opinion program.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Second opinion service included on most plans</li>
    <li>Access to world-leading specialists</li>
    <li>Coordination of medical records and imaging</li>
    <li>Written report from specialist</li>
    <li>Multiple specialties covered</li>
    <li>International expert network</li>
    <li>Cancer-specific second opinion programs</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Premium pricing. Best second opinion services on higher-tier plans. Worth it for peace of mind on major diagnoses.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/bupa-global">Read our full Bupa Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Cigna Global — Strong Specialist Network</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers good second opinion access through their specialist network.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Second opinion services on premium plans</li>
    <li>Wide specialist network globally</li>
    <li>Good coordination services</li>
    <li>Telehealth second opinions available</li>
    <li>Medical records coordination</li>
    <li>Multiple specialties covered</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Not all plans include second opinions. Premium plans have best access. Good option with comprehensive coverage.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our full Cigna Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Aetna International — US Specialist Access</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna International provides access to top US medical centers.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access to US centers of excellence</li>
    <li>Mayo Clinic, Cleveland Clinic connections</li>
    <li>Strong for cancer second opinions</li>
    <li>Complex case coordination</li>
    <li>Medical advocacy services</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> US-focused expertise. Best if you want American specialists. Select plans only.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/aetna-international">Read our full Aetna International review</a></p>

  <h2 id="how-it-works">How Second Opinion Services Work</h2>

  <h3>The Process</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Request:</strong> Contact your insurer about second opinion</li>
    <li><strong>Records:</strong> They coordinate collecting your medical records</li>
    <li><strong>Matching:</strong> Specialist matched to your condition</li>
    <li><strong>Review:</strong> Expert reviews your case (in-person or remote)</li>
    <li><strong>Report:</strong> You receive written opinion with recommendations</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Types of Second Opinions</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>In-person consultation:</strong> See specialist directly</li>
    <li><strong>Remote/telehealth:</strong> Video consultation with expert</li>
    <li><strong>Written review:</strong> Expert reviews records and provides report</li>
    <li><strong>Pathology review:</strong> Slides/samples reviewed by specialists</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>What's Usually Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Specialist consultation fees</li>
    <li>Medical records coordination</li>
    <li>Pathology and imaging review</li>
    <li>Written report and recommendations</li>
    <li>Sometimes travel to specialist (premium plans)</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Major Decisions Deserve Expert Review"
    description="Don't face serious diagnoses without specialist consultation."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
  />

  <h2 id="when-to-seek">When to Seek Second Opinions</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={scenarioColumns} rows={scenarioRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Always Consider For</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Cancer diagnoses (staging, treatment approach)</li>
    <li>Major surgery recommendations</li>
    <li>Rare or unusual conditions</li>
    <li>When you're not confident in diagnosis</li>
    <li>When recommended treatment has significant risks</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Good Idea For</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Chronic condition management changes</li>
    <li>Mental health medication decisions</li>
    <li>Orthopedic surgery recommendations</li>
    <li>When treatment isn't working</li>
    <li>Before expensive procedures</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Less Critical For</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Routine, well-established procedures</li>
    <li>Clear-cut diagnoses with standard treatment</li>
    <li>Minor conditions</li>
    <li>When you have high confidence in your doctor</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Do I need my doctor's permission to get a second opinion?</h3>
  <p>
    No. It's your right to seek additional opinions about your health. Good doctors welcome second opinions and don't feel threatened. Your insurer can help coordinate without involving your original doctor if preferred.
  </p>

  <h3>Will my doctor be offended if I seek a second opinion?</h3>
  <p>
    Professional doctors understand and support patients seeking second opinions, especially for serious diagnoses. If your doctor is offended, that itself may be a red flag. Second opinions are standard practice for major medical decisions.
  </p>

  <h3>Are second opinions covered for any condition?</h3>
  <p>
    Usually for serious conditions or major treatment decisions. Routine issues typically don't qualify. Check your policy for specifics. Most programs focus on cancer, surgery, chronic conditions, and rare diseases.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I get a second opinion from a doctor in another country?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, international health insurance often connects you with specialists globally. This is especially valuable for accessing experts in rare conditions or world-leading treatment centers regardless of where you live.
  </p>

  <h3>How long does getting a second opinion take?</h3>
  <p>
    Typically 1-3 weeks for non-urgent cases. Urgent cases can be expedited. The process includes gathering records, matching a specialist, and scheduling review. Remote reviews may be faster than in-person consultations.
  </p>

  <h3>What if the second opinion disagrees with the first?</h3>
  <p>
    This happens in 10-30% of cases. You can discuss both opinions with your primary doctor, seek a third opinion if needed, or choose the approach you're most confident in. The goal is making an informed decision, not necessarily finding agreement.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This content is for informational purposes only. Second opinion services and coverage vary by plan and insurer. We are not insurance brokers or medical professionals. Always verify current coverage directly with insurers.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
